# Repo and Deploy Source of Truth

- Before any commit/push, identify whether the target is the root monorepo (`origin`) or the standalone frontend mirror (`frontend` remote → `ai-native-ip-frontend`). The Next.js app lives at **`frontend/`** in the monorepo and is synced to the mirror with **`git subtree split --prefix=frontend`** then **`git push frontend split-frontend:main`** (see team workflow).
- Never assume deploy source by filename only; verify actual tracked files with Git in the active repo.
- When user says "push/deploy", confirm and state explicitly:
  - which repository remote will receive the push
  - which branch will be pushed
  - which directory/repo is the deploy source (`frontend` for frontend deploys).
- **Railway backend:** This GitHub repo’s default branch is **`master`** (`origin/HEAD` → `master`). Railway deploys from **`master`** unless you changed it in Railway Settings. Pushes to **`main` alone do not trigger Railway** in the default setup.
- Do not mix unrelated commits: push **`master`** to **`origin`** for the monorepo backend deploy; push the subtree branch to **`frontend`** for Netlify when the site is wired to `ai-native-ip-frontend`.
- After push, report the exact commit SHA and repo/branch so user can verify deployment source.
